# IMDb rating by genre (boxplot)

plt.title('IMDb Ratings by Genre')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

In [42]:
# Avg IMDb Rating by Year
avg_rating_by_year = df_original.groupby('release_year')['imdb_score'].mean()

plt.figure(figsize=(14,6))
avg_rating_by_year.plot(marker='o', color='green')
plt.xticks(ticks=avg_rating_by_year.index, rotation=90, ha='right')
plt.title('Average IMDb Rating by Year')
plt.xlabel('Release Year')
plt.ylabel('IMDb Rating')
plt.grid(True)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show

In [44]:
# Genre popularity over time
genre_trend = df_exploded.groupby(['release_year', 'genre']).size().reset_index(name='count')
top_genres =  df_exploded['genre'].value_counts().head(5).index
plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
for g in top_genres:
    subset = genre_trend[genre_trend['genre'] == g]
    plt.plot(subset['release_year'], subset['count'], label=g)
    plt.title('Top Genres Over Time')
    plt.legend()
    plt.show()

In [62]:
# trend over time

df_sorted = df_exploded.sort_values('release_year').reset_index(drop=True)
df_sorted['rolling_avg'] = df_sorted['imdb_score'].rolling(window=100).mean()

# plot 
plt.figure(figsize=(10,5))
plt.plot(df_sorted['rolling_avg'], color='purple')
plt.title('Rolling Avg IMDb Rating (per 100 titles)')
plt.xlabel('Title Index (sorted by release year)')
plt.ylabel('IMDb Rating')
plt.grid=True 
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

print(df_sorted['rolling_avg'].min())
print(df_sorted['rolling_avg'].max())
print(df_sorted['rolling_avg'].mean())
